SIMPLE: thickhead
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thickhead
<hw>Thick"head`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
thick-headed or stupid person.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of several species of
Australian singing birds of the genus <gen>Pachycephala</gen>. The males
of some of the species are bright-colored. Some of the species are
popularly called <altname>thrushes</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thick-headed</ent>⟦br⟧
